EPODE IX

‘WHEN shall we have our feast, Maecenas, in your great house ’ at home, to celebrate Caesar's victory as we celebrated the defeat of Sextus Pompeius a little while ago? Oh, the shame to think of Roman soldiers in Cleopatra's effeminate camp! Even Galatian horsemen deserted her, and her fleet would not fight.
